reviews.snippet:
Vibe Rooms is exactly what a karaoke bar should be; fun, friendly, welcoming and down-to-earth!
Too many karaoke bars in Budapest are pretentious and over-priced. Vibe Rooms is the opposite! As soon as you enter, you are made to feel like you are at a friend's party having a great time, which instantly makes you relax and feel at ease. You can let loose in one of the intimate private rooms or join a sing-along in the main bar, where the owner and staff are just as likely to be crooning away as the guests are.
We recently had a great night at Vibe Rooms and it was honestly one of the most evening's we have had in ages. I'd recommend Vibe Rooms to anyone who wants a no-frills, super-friendly, chilled out time!
(The welcome shots for the private room was another plus too!)

extracted_snippet.translated: I don't recommend it to anyone. We had a bachelorette party there. The story started there, when the confirmation email specifically stated that we should show up at least 15 minutes before the start. That's what happened, we went there at 5:45 PM. The door was already wide open, we could easily go in. One of the colleagues was putting on her makeup, asked her in a not-so-friendly way what we were doing here, we said we had a reservation. To this we received the answer that we could go in soon. We were about to sit in the waiting room, then the colleague not very kindly told us that we should leave because they weren't open yet, and as we could see, the chairs hadn't even been taken down. The evening started with a fairly "positive" impression. We rented the Large room for 2 hours, which can be rented out for up to 8 people. I don't want to know how big their Medium room is, but it's probably terribly small. I was convinced I ordered nachos, but when we got there, they said it wasn't included in the reservation, so they didn't order either. The microphones are crap, they only started working halfway through, but if you don't use them, they're probably worth more. The supposedly advertised soundproofing is pretty much zero, if the music isn't playing, you can easily hear the singers in the room next to you. The VIP Lounge, as we saw, is actually nothing more than a waiting room with 3 tables and, let's say, 10 chairs. The food and drink selection was quite poor, and the menu in the room was in water or alcohol, I don't know what, even though they were open at the time... Of course, you have to pay for everything in advance when you get there. I always check Google reviews, but this time it didn't work and I regret it. Zero hospitality, and I say I'll blame it on someone having a bad day, it happens, but the place itself is terrible, the pictures posted don't reflect reality and the service is really not worth the price. On top of that, they overcharged us by 4000 HUF, but I decided, after reading the feedback and the impression I got from the staff, not to bother with it. It was expensive student money, but I'll definitely avoid them from afar in the future. Don't make the same mistake.

There were 7 of us in the large room, the website recommends the room for up to 8 people, but we couldn't actually sit down for 7 of us :O The room consists of 2 sofas and a TV, there's almost no space outside, and the 2 sofas are for 3 people, so one of us had to stand. I very rarely write negative reviews, but since you get a free 5-star review right after you enter and you haven't even been to the room, which many people don't modify or delete, I thought I'd write about the real experience.
We had a good time, but we had each other to thank for that, and I'm only giving it 2 stars because of the staff, otherwise it would be 1 star...
